external_knowledge:
- "Currently active users" refers to users with an active_status of 1; 
- "Moderate to high access levels" means an access level greater than 1; 
- Access in the "past three months" means access since the date three months prior to the current date ('now','-3 month').

- Users accessing more than five different schools in more than two different ways may be considered highly active or power users; 
- The total enrollment of the accessed schools may indicate the scope of data each user is working with; 
- The average founding year could hint at the type of schools a user is interested in (e.g., newer vs. older schools).

sql:
SELECT schools.*, access_logs.*
FROM schools
INNER JOIN access_logs ON schools.school_id = access_logs.school_id;
